<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
                  <br>Superhero Sakusen (a.k.a. Super Hero Operations) is an RPG released in 1999 by Banpresto for the Sony PlayStation. The game spawned a sequel, known as Super Hero Operations: Diedal's Ambition. The game is considered part of the Super Robot Wars series due to the characters Ingram Prisken and Viletta Vadim who originally debuted in the game alongside the mech R-Gun, which later included in Super Robot Wars Alpha.
                  <br><br>The theme song for the game was performed by Ichirou Mizuki and Mitsuko Horie.
                  <br><br>STORY:
                  <br>The story is a mix and match of all robot universes, plot events such as Devil Gundam's appearence from G Gundam or Ultraman blasting away more monsters are mixed beautifully. You can be running from Devil Gundam in a forest and suddenly get stopped by someone like Heero Yui (from Gundam Wing).
                  <br><br>GAMEPLAY:
                  <br>The game plays like a tyical RPG, turn based fighting with the robots against the enemy. Robots and pilots gain experince points.
                  <br><br>CHARACTERS:
                  <br>The game features playable characters from different Tokusatsu and Anime series. The following series are included in this game:
                  <br>- Mobile Fighter G Gundam
                  <br>- Mobile Suit Gundam Wing
                  <br>- Ultraman
                  <br>- Ultra Seven
                  <br>- The Return of Ultraman
                  <br>- Ultraman Ace
                  <br>- Ultraman Taro
                  <br>- Ultraman Leo
                  <br>- Kaiketsu Zubat
                  <br>- Kikaider
                  <br>- Kikaider 01
                  <br>- Choujinki Metalder
                  <br>- Uchuu Keiji Gavan
                  <br>- Uchuu Keiji Sharivan
                  <br>- Uchuu Keiji Shaider
                  <br>- Banpresto original characters
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>New and old special effects character of many Ultraman, Space Sheriff Gavan, Kikaider, and superhuman machine Metaruda comes up! * Reproduce the Special Move in the original! CG battle screen with power. I adopt a cut-in system that goes beyond the "Super Robot Wars"! * I direct the presence of the original screen over field of 3D rendering attention to detail, enliven the battle, such as "multi-screen Battlefield!" * Super Ultra mechanical Hawk No. 1 and jet Beetle, such as Gundam Wing comes up number. Demonstration and makeover Hero starting or scene number available!
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>SCIFI & Futuristic themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

